<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880705-0012 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: General Refractories Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GRX </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   General Refractories Co. said a company controlled by its chairman extended the Thursday expiration of an offer to take the Philadelphia concern private for $20.50 a share, or $38.2 million.    Raymond G. Perelman, chairman, president and chief executive officer of General Refractories, is making the offer through his Belmont Industries Inc., also based in Philadelphia. No new expiration date was set for the offer, but Belmont said it hoped to conclude the process by the middle of this month.    Shares of General Refractories, which mines minerals and makes heat-resistant materials for use in furnaces, closed Friday at $21.25, unchanged, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading. </TEXT></DOC>